03/09/2004
ATHENS, Greece -- Alpha, Greece's largest private bank, said Thursday (2 September) that up to 25 billion euros could be added to the country's GDP by 2008 as a result of the Olympics. Greece already added 9 billion euros to its GDP between 2000 and 2004, the bank said, stressing that the Games helped promote Greek products around the world and positioned Greece as a major tourist attraction. (AFP - 02/09/04)
